Package ohos.agp.render

Class ColorMatrix

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.agp.render.ColorMatrix

  • public class ColorMatrix
extends Object
    Transforms the alpha and color values of a PixelMap object.

    This class provides a 4 x 5 matrix of floating-point numbers to implement translation, scaling, or saturation adjustment on color vectors. The following is an example of ColorMatrix instance: 

    
 M = [ m00, m01, m02, m03, m04,
       m10, m11, m12, m13, m14,
       m20, m21, m22, m23, m24,
       m30, m31, m32, m33, m34 ]
    A color vector is represented as [R, G, B, A, 1]. R, G, and B indicate the color value, and A indicates the alpha value. By adding vector 1, you will be able to represent translation of the color vector by matrix multiplication. After the transformation, the color vector is as follows: 
    
 R = m00*R + m01*G + m02*B + m03*A + m04
 G = m10*R + m11*G + m12*B + m13*A + m14
 B = m20*R + m21*G + m22*B + m23*A + m24
 A = m30*R + m31*G + m32*B + m33*A + m34

    1

      • reset

        public void reset​()
        Resets a colorMatrix instance to an identity matrix.

        The identity matrix is defined as follows: 

         [ 1 0 0 0 0 - red vector
   0 1 0 0 0 - green vector
   0 0 1 0 0 - blue vector
   0 0 0 1 0 ] - alpha vector
